        "value": 6,
        "tolerance": 0
      },
      "difficulty": 1,
      "hints": {
        "default": [
          "\\(\\frac{3}{4}\\times8\\) means \\(\\frac{3}{4}\\) of 8.",
          "First find \\(\\frac{1}{4}\\) of 8, then multiply by 3.",
          "\\(8\\div4=2\\), so \\(\\frac{3}{4}\\times8=3\\times2=?\\)."
